Class WorldCell

All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.loading.Unloadable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Nameable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.Stringable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.StringSource, Outline, Bounded, Intersectable, Bordered, Comparable<Region<WorldCell>>
public class WorldCell extends Region<WorldCell> implements com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.loading.Unloadable
A world cell is a square Region in a WorldGrid. The actual layout of this cell in a grid is handled by GridCell which is a rectangle in a Grid. These classes are found in a separate utility package in the mesakit-map project.

Identifiers

A WorldCell has a reference to the world grid that owns it which can be retrieved with worldGrid(). It also has a convenience method to access the WorldGraph that owns the world grid. The cell can be identified by a WorldCell.WorldCellIdentifier retrieved from worldCellIdentifier().

Graph Data

The data for a world cell is contained in a Folder accessed with folder() and the specific data for the cell can be accessed with cellGraphFile() and cellGraph(). The size of data in byes is available with fileSize() and t estimated size in memory with memorySize().

Neighboring Cells

World cells that are next to this world cell can be retrieved with neighbors() and if this cell should itself be included, with neighborsAndThis().
